programme.title: Barista
programme.sub-title: The battle for the perfect cup is on
programme.desc: Enter the high-pressure world of coffee creation with five contestants at the World Barista Championship. Enter the high-pressure world of competitive coffee creation with five contestants at the World Barista Championship. A craft that is both artistry and chemistry, but not always taken seriously, these baristas pursue this path out of pure passion.

programme.title: Arriving in Moscow
programme.desc: The b-boys arrive in Moscow for the BC One finals. After exploring the city, they meet Rakaa, the event emcee. The b-boys arrive in Moscow and immediately take off for a photo shoot. After exploring the city, all three are greeted by Rakaa, the event emcee who announces the battles. Now there's nothing left to do but wait for the competition to begin.

programme.title: Barefoot skiing
programme.desc: Jamie O'Brien and the crew are still in Waco, Texas, trying out some new water sports. Jamie O'Brien and the crew are still in Waco, Texas, catching barrels at the new wave pool then hit the cable park and take on some jumps with wompers, skis and more. Then they try their hands–or feet–at barefoot skiing.

programme.title: Evan Faulks
programme.desc: Evan Faulks builds homes for a living, but his life’s foundation is his family and big wave surfing. Evan Faulks spends his day building and renovating homes. Through this, he’s able to support his family, improve his community of Maroubra, Australia, and spend his free time chasing the giant swells of nearby Cape Fear.

programme.title: King Lines: Part I
programme.desc: Champion climber Chris Sharma starts a quest to make first ascents of the greatest unclimbed walls on Earth. Chris Sharma, the world’s strongest climber, embarks on a quest to make first ascents of Earth's greatest unclimbed walls. On his journey, he finds a massive arch rising out of the Mediterranean Sea that could be the most difficult ascent ever.

programme.title: Roraima
programme.desc: A trio of climbers launch an expedition to Mount Roraima, a South American peak shrouded in legend. Climbing partners Kurt Albert and Holger Heuber don't know what they're in for when they join competitive climbing superstar Stefan Glowacz for an expedition to Mount Roraima, a steep-walled South American peak shrouded in both rainforest and legend.

programme.title: The Signal Hill Speed Run
programme.desc: The contest that established downhill skateboarding was a festival of speed, partying and danger. A ridiculously steep hill in California was the stage for downhill skateboarding's first contest and it quickly became the epicentre of the absurd new sport. The Signal Hill Speed Run was a festival of innovation, speed and danger.

programme.title: ABC of... Parkour
programme.desc: Learn the language, moves and magic of the artistry of running and jumping over natural and urban terrain. Parkour, the sport that involves running, jumping and climbing over and through natural and urban terrain, pushes the body to the limit. It’s unpredictable and made great by the artistry of its athletes. Learn about its language, moves and magic.

programme.title: Continental Drift
programme.desc: The Enduro World Series arrives in Australia. Curtis Keene and the team do their best to prepare for race day. After a disappointing race in Rotorua, New Zealand, Curtis Keene and Jared Graves arrive in Tasmania, Australia to spend a week preparing. But despite their best efforts, unforeseen developments leave them adjusting strategies at the last minute.

programme.title: Living Forever
programme.desc: American rapper GZA is on a quest to understand the age-old human desire to live forever. In his quest to understand the human desire to live forever, American rapper GZA finds out how bodies are stored in Arizona, visits a California lab studying the immortal hydra, and goes to Vermont’s transhumanist Terasem Foundation.

programme.title: Séan Garnier vs The World
programme.sub-title: From the streets to the stage to the top
programme.desc: Freestyle football has been Séan Garnier’s ticket to the world, but success never comes without sacrifice. From the streets to the pinnacle of freestyle success, Séan’s Garnier’s prodigal journey has been one of self-discovery through football.

programme.title: Asia Rising
programme.desc: Seen through the eyes of a diverse group, we take a look at the fast-paced success of Asian hip-hop. With the help of record label 88rising, we look at six different artists from six different backgrounds, all within Asia, as they share their thoughts on the recent rise of hip-hop in the region.

programme.title: Mountain Biking Will Ruin Your Life
programme.desc: Mountain biking can be addicting, and for both pros and amateurs there’s no better fix than Whistler, Canada. For those who can't break into the pro ranks, travelling with the Enduro World Series as a photographer might be the next best thing. And for mountain bikers of all sorts, there’s no better place to go than Whistler, Canada.

programme.title: Justen Allport
programme.desc: Justen Allport is a firefighter, but his passion for the big waves burns eternal. Justen Allport is used to danger. Being a firefighter would provide most with their fill of adrenaline, but to Justen it’s a means to an end. He’s been riding big waves since childhood, and now he charges the giant slabs of Cape Fear, Australia.

programme.title: Evan Faulks
programme.desc: Evan Faulks builds homes for a living, but his life’s foundation is his family and big wave surfing. Evan Faulks spends his day building and renovating homes. Through this, he’s able to support his family, improve his community of Maroubra, Australia, and spend his free time chasing the giant swells of nearby Cape Fear.

programme.title: Jack Kingsley
programme.desc: He holds down three different jobs to give him the freedom to go surf when the waves are huge. Jack Kingsley is a man who gets out of his comfort zone. That has landed him in a wide variety of jobs: carpet layer, ju-jitsu teacher, stunt man. It was this drive to try new things that tempted him to surf the huge waves of Australia’s Cape Fear.

programme.title: Exploring Madagascar
programme.desc: Slade Prestwich, Frank Solomon and Grant 'Twiggy' Baker embark on an epic surf adventure to Madagascar. Slade Prestwich, Frank Solomon and Grant 'Twiggy' Baker embark on an epic adventure to the previously unsurfed island of Madagascar. They chart new territory, searching for new waves to ride and meeting with local villagers.

programme.title: Hanging Spear
programme.desc: World class whitewater kayakers Steve Fisher and Pat Keller explore the Hanging Spear Gorge. Join world class whitewater kayakers Steve Fisher and Pat Keller as they explore the Hanging Spear Gorge of the Opalescent River, the highest source of the Hudson and the deepest part of New York State’s High Peaks wilderness.

programme.title: On the Roots of Cleopatra
programme.desc: Wakeskater Brian Grubb sessions at the pristine Cleopatra's Pool at the ruins of Hierapolis in Turkey. Always searching for unique places to wakeskate, Brian Grubb sessions at the pristine Cleopatra's Pool, a mineral-rich bath in the ruins of the ancient city of Hierapolis near modern day Denizli, Turkey.
